12.03	Anastylosis	Anastylosis	Anastylosis (from the Ancient Greek: ; = "again", and = "to erect (a stela or building)") is an archaeological term for a reconstruction technique whereby a ruined building or monument is restored using the original architectural elements to the greatest degree possible. It is also sometimes used to refer to a similar technique for restoring broken pottery and other small objects.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a8/Celsus-Bibliothek2.jpg/250px-Celsus-Bibliothek2.jpg
